Source: plx
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.7.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/commandprompt/plx

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-plx
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-plx
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Transpile multiple procedural dialects to PL/pgSQL
 plx transpiles functions written in Ruby, PHP, JavaScript, TypeScript, Python,
 Go, COBOL, Oracle PL/SQL, or Transact-SQL syntax into PL/pgSQL at CREATE
 FUNCTION time and executes them with PostgreSQL's standard PL/pgSQL runtime.
